The paper discusses the development of autonomous software agents for managing and defending against cyber threats in a battlefield environment. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges associated with developing such agents, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper focuses on the Internet of Battlefield Things, which could fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
